JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s President Jacob Zuma said on Tuesday the country&#8217;s fiscal policy would remain unchanged after his cabinet reshuffle and that his ministers would reach out to international investors to assure them of this after S&amp;P downgraded the country&#8217;s credit level to &#8220;junk&#8221;. Zuma dismissed the respected Pravin Gordhan as finance minister in a midnight cabinet reshuffle on Thursday that shocked local markets and triggered protests from within his own party, business and opposition parties.The rand pared some its losses after Zuma&#8217;s remarks in a speech at a function held at state-owned Transnet. 